    public enum ConfIterateFlags

    Enumeration flags us by CdbSubscription.diffIterate(int,CdbDiffIterate,EnumSet,Object) to control the behavior of iterate over changes made in CDB data.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ITER_WANT_PREV

        public static final ConfIterateFlags ITER_WANT_PREV
        Include the previous value for modification of a leaf/leaf-list value. If the flags is provided to CdbSubscription.diffIterate(int ,CdbDiffIterate,EnumSet,Object) The old value is supplied to the call to CdbDiffIterate.iterate(ConfObject[], DiffIterateOperFlag, ConfObject,ConfObject,Object) if a value have changed.

        For operational data subscriptions, the ITER_WANT_PREV flag is ignored, and old value is always null - there is no equivalent to CdbDBType.CDB_PRE_COMMIT_RUNNING that holds "old" operational data method. This option is default in CdbSubscription.diffIterate(int, CdbDiffIterate) which means that the flag needs not to be passed explicitly.

      • ITER_WANT_ANCESTOR_DELETE

        public static final ConfIterateFlags ITER_WANT_ANCESTOR_DELETE
        Control if the deleted of a ancestor will trigger a subscription iteration.

        The flag ITER_WANT_ANCESTOR_DELETE is passed to diffIterate method which specifies that a subscription should be triggered because an ancestor was deleted subscription will also generate a call to iterate, and in this case kp will be the path that was actually deleted. This option is not default in CdbSubscription.diffIterate(int, CdbDiffIterate) which means that the flag needs to be passed explicitly.

      • ITER_WANT_ATTR

        public static final ConfIterateFlags ITER_WANT_ATTR
        This is flag that only has meaning in the maapi case. If set, the iteration will also go over attribute values. In such cases the DiffIterateOperFlag will be set to DiffIterateOperFlag.MOP_ATTR_SET in the iterator and the new and old values will be of type ConfAttributeValue

      • ITER_WANT_LEAF_LIST_AS_LEAF

        public static final ConfIterateFlags ITER_WANT_LEAF_LIST_AS_LEAF
        Leaf-list nodes will cause invocations of iterate() as for leafs and not as for lists, i.e. a single invocation per leaf-list with keypath pointing to leaf-list node with "value" set to ConfList instance rather than multiple invocations with keypath pointing to individual leaf-list elements. Attributes on leaf-list elements will be ignored when this flag is used.
